originalText.text: I read the reviews and convinced myself I was going to be screwed. I stayed at the EVEN and braced for the worst. I thought of even parking outside of the city to avoid this garage. When I got my car back, I expected a bunch of bogus fees, scratches, a one-hour wait. Nope, none of that! These bad reviews must be written by competitors. I paid $55/day for 24hrs. Not a penny more, and a great price considering it is Christmastime. It took them 5 minutes to retrieve my car. No scratches, and gas was at the same level that I left it. The gentlemen were also super friendly and helpful. The only thing I am upset about, is that I let the bad reviews make me toil for days about picking up my vehicle. This is a greatly ran operation, and I would definitely recommend!

originalText.text: I’m not sure why there are so many negative reviews, maybe there’s been a management change? I had an excellent experience with this garage. They were super super nice, priced as any other garage in Manhattan, and wouldn’t even take my tip until I forced it. I’ll def park here again when I’m around!

originalText.text: Run by criminals. For less than 1 hour parking wound up charging $50 despite the sign saying 1 hour parking would be 31+tax. Said our midsize vehicle was “oversized” (there’s no oversized surcharge advertised on their price sign). When bringing the car out, they blasted past us and then knocked on the window for us to leave as we were trying to get our baby settled. Would give zero stars if I could, don’t trust your vehicle in this lot, there’s plenty other on the same block.

originalText.text:
I arrived at this location at 9:12am to park to avoid public transportation during this crisis. I am a essential worker who comes to work everyday for the UN. I tried to park my car and was told that it will be an additional $50 than what I would usually pay for parking. I have been a long time customer at this location over the last few weekends and I have never been quoted. When I asked why there was no explanation , when I tried to explain this is price gouging and illegal. I was told IF YOU ARE AFRAID STAY HOME. I come outside everyday to work because I am needed, I risk my health and my families to be told “IF I AM AFRAID STAY HOME.” The disrespect is unbelievable when I’m risking my health to do my job. The essential workers are needed and to know this the treatment we receive. Over priced items and services, nasty comments and disrespect.

The world is going through a crisis and as humans we should look out for one another but this business seems to only carry about theirselves. I usually come here 3x a month and this will be the last time I do business with this company. BEWARE

- TW
